article.headline: Evansville 65, Southeast Missouri State 45
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Art Stalbergs scored 16 points on 7-of-8 shooting -- including 2-of-3 3-pointers -- to lead Evansville to a 65-45 win over Southeast Missouri on Monday night. Kyle Anslinger had 13 points and shot 3-of-7 from 3-point-range for the Purple Aces (3-2). Matt Webster finished with 11 points. Bradley Strickland grabbed eight rebounds to contribute to a 40-37 Evansville advantage on the boards. JaJuan Maxwell, who finished with 11 points, was the only player in double figures for the Redhawks (2-4), who were outscored 18-6 after turnovers and 13-7 on second-chance points. The game was tied only once at 1-1 in the opening minutes, but the lead changed eight times. Evansville led 25-22 at the break.
